The paper deals with the problem of extracting tabular data from scanned document images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed solution involves the use of deep learning models, which is a popular approach in computer vision and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of semantic features to improve model performance, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL).
